# 📖 EsBook32
A minimalist, distraction-free e-reader built for the **ESP32-S3** and **SSD1306 OLED** displays. No backlight, no notifications, just you and your `.txt` files.

## 🛠 Hardware Setup
* **MCU:** ESP32-S3 (Optimized for Heltec WiFi LoRa 32 V4)
* **Display:** 128x64 I2C OLED (SSD1306)
* **Input:** Single Momentary Button (using the `OneButton` library)
* **Filesystem:** LittleFS (Internal Flash)

---

## 🕹 Navigation & Controls
The entire interface is managed through a **single button**. 

| Action | Menu Navigation | Inside a Book |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Single Click** | Move Cursor Down | Next Page |
| **Double Click** | Move Cursor Up / Exit | Previous Page |
| **Long Press** | Select / Confirm | Open Pause Menu |

> **Note:** Double-clicking while in the **WiFi Upload** portal will shut down the Access Point and return you to the Settings menu.

---

## 📂 Uploading Books
The device acts as its own server. To add new reading material:

1.  Navigate to **Settings** -> **WiFi Upload**.
2.  Connect your phone or computer to the WiFi network: **`EsBook32_Setup`**.
3.  Open a web browser and go to: **`http://192.168.4.1`**
4.  Select your `.txt` file and hit **Upload**.
5.  Once the screen says "SUCCESS," double-click the device button to return to your library.

---

## ⚠️ Caveats & Limitations
* **File Format:** Strictly supports **`.txt`** files. Formatting (bold, italics, etc.) is not supported.
* **Encoding:** Ensure your files are saved in **UTF-8** encoding. Files with a "BOM" (Byte Order Mark) might display a few "junk" characters on the first line.
* **Flat Filesystem:** This version uses a flat root structure. Folders are not supported; all files should be uploaded directly to the root.
* **File Size:** While the ESP32 can handle large files, extremely massive texts (multi-megabyte) may cause the initial page indexing to feel sluggish.
* **Deep Sleep:** The device will enter deep sleep after **2 minutes** of inactivity to save battery. Press the hardware **RST** or **PRG** button (depending on your board) to wake it up.

---

## 💾 Progress Saving
EsBook32 automatically creates a `.pos` file for every book you read. This file stores your current byte offset so you never lose your place, even after a full power-down or deep sleep.

